tweet: @jakewertz @UpshotNYT Yes, I've had discussions about this with numerous copy editors, and while even AP Style has given conflicting direction on it, copy editors at the Trib always went with two words for this form of the question. Here's a good discussion of it:  https://t.co/z3VRLB1L95

name: Liam T.A. Ford
tweet: @jakewertz @UpshotNYT No, it's not "Whatever Happened to Baby Jane?" Or "Whatever happened..." to anything. "What ever happened" is a cant phrase, but it is a phrase and has a different meaning from "whatever..."

name: Liam T.A. Ford
tweet: @jakewertz @UpshotNYT No, it's an actual question, even though the uses seem similar. The phrase is different from the emphasizing use of "Whatever" you're implying.

name: The Henry Ford

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: When designers pay attention to those on the margins, the result is products that work better for everyone. It results in a world in which fewer people finds themselves mismatched with their environments. It's one way that designers can make for a better world. #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/a4Ur1blFF7

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Historically, designers have created for the median‚Äîfor those few people who fit the "average." Who is left on the margins? It's the majority of people‚Äîand often children, those with disabilities, and aging adults. #THFCuratorChat

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Michael Graves passed away in 2015, but his design firm, @MGravesDesign, honors his legacy and continues to design high-quality objects for a wide range of bodies and abilities, including through a recent partnership with CVS. #THFCuratorChat    https://t.co/WrkDWwAFFA

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Graves redesigned the wheelchair‚Äîa chair that had seen little change since the 1930s. Comfort was the focus. The Transport Chair features adjustable components, easy maneuverability, and intuitive operation, as well as quality finishes and bold color. #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/1D6vcqtJ28

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: @MGravesDesign also teamed up with Stryker, a medical technologies company, to reimagine a hospital patient's experience. Spurred by one of his many extended hospital stays, Michael Graves remarked, ‚ÄúIt was far too ugly for me to die in there!‚Äù  https://t.co/KsROWBW2SW

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Graves focused on creating canes with ergonomic grips and customizable lengths  that are foldable and lightweight. These are dignified objects that honor the user. #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/zIp1DUhwxm

name: The Henry Ford

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Moore disguised herself off and on for over three years‚Äîconducting research and becoming a sought-after expert in design for aging populations. name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Moore even put baby oil in her eyes to blur her vision, stuffed wax in her ears to muffle sound, and bound her body to restrict movement. She then went out into the world‚Äîobserving, interacting, and connecting with people as an elderly woman. #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/rKEeuBvoJN

name: The Henry Ford

name: The Henry Ford

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: The OXO Good Grips Swivel Peeler was introduced in 1990. Despite its cost (nearly triple the traditional peeler), it sold well. This relatively simple improvement to a classic tool increased usability for a wide range of people. #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/LINdnB6CHf

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: The peeler was difficult to grip, especially when applying force. Sam and Betsey realized there was an opportunity to improve this object and called a friend, Davin Stowell of design consultancy Smart Design, and asked him to prototype an easier-to-user peeler. #THFCuratorChat

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: The story goes that Sam and Betsey Farber were enjoying retirement in the 1980s. One day, Betsey was peeling an apple tart and having some difficulty‚Äîshe was using a traditional stainless steel vegetable peeler and had some arthritis in her hands. #THFCuratorChat

name: The Henry Ford
tweet: Next, we'll focus on a classic story of Universal Design‚ÄîOXO Good Grips. As has been pointed out, even the name "OXO" adheres to Universal Design concepts, as it can be read forward, backwards, or upside down! #THFCuratorChat  https://t.co/ysx0KJ4mjm

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Next up ‚Äî after being interrupted ‚Äî a speaker calls the board "a three-ring circus".  She also says it is ridiculous how "unevenly [Ford] is applying policies" such as who he gavels down and who he doesn't.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: So, apart from Grapevine-Colleyville's Board of Trustee President Casey Ford admitting he avoids open records, the executive session didn't result in any actions.  The board is hearing from some STEM students (sorry, I missed it) and recognizing campus emergency managers.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: @GCISD Board of Trustee President Casey Ford basically admits that he does not put information in text/writing to Trustee Becky St. John because he does not want it to become open record.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford accuses St. John of being unwilling to meet. St. John implies that she wants all communication in writing...and Ford basically says some information is too sensitive for that.  (*This is alarming...he is basically admitting to avoiding documenting communication).

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Trustee Jorge Rodr√≠guez also weighs in passionately and agrees with St. John that this is in fact a witch hunt and accuses Ford of being unprofessional and asks him to never treat him this way, embarrass the board + district like this, etc.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Okay, wild minute: An audience member clapped after St. John criticized Ford's handling of these allegations and Ford paused the meeting, said "we'll sit in silence here" while he asked other audience members to out who clapped so they can be thrown out.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Trustee Coley Canter asks the board to take this as an opportunity to agree to disagree and proposes the board take character training or resign members' ethics pledges.  Ford recommends St. John "take the high road" and issue an apology.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Some context: St. John has served on the board for 13 years. Ford was elected in Nov. 2010 and Kathy Florence Spradley was elected in May 2022.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford moves the conversation on to the next allegation (after determining that the board has proved what she did, but St. John alleges she didn't).   The next allegation is that she (falsely) accused the district's counsel (lawyer) of sleeping during the last meeting.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: St. John asks another board member to weigh in, and is interrupted and is told that is inappropriate.  A community member erupts and says that Ford is not calling decorum on the board members' back-and-forth.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford asks members of the public not to laugh (or make noise or clap, etc.) or they will be removed.   St. John now asks not to be interrupted. She said that emails accusing her of the actions Ford outlines is false.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: When he has completed his statement, St. John calls his statement "a pretty prepared statement" and asks if he had intended to read it aloud to the public anyways.  Ford asks St. John not to "speculate" on his statement, which is met by laughs from the crowd.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford says that during GCISD's Board of Trustees last meeting, St. John was witnessed calling another board member a "b----" and a "f-- b---".

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford is interrupted by a meeting attendee who says she can't hear, but he asks her multiple times to be quiet and says he doesn't control the sound.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: Ford adds that he hoped to have the discussion privately so that St. John's "behavior might change."  He continues by reading the board's ethics pledge.

name: Meghan Mangrum
tweet: St. John said she asked Board of Trustees President Casey Ford why she was on the agenda and said he would not tell her why.  Ford says he wanted the discussion to be private because he doesn't believe in "airing the board's dirty laundry publicly."

tweet: A post-script thanks to the Edison and Ford Winter Estates for this history of the Sialia:    https://t.co/Lh9kl1u5As

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Side note:  There are newspaper reports of Ford‚Äôs son, Edsel, crashing a yacht called the ‚ÄúSialia‚Äù in 1929. But this may have been a different vessel.  The official ownership log of the original Sialia makes no mention of Edsel Ford. A little unclear‚Ä¶   https://t.co/4qN7DVLvnc

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Ford later tried to retool the Sialia to improve its speed.   But his ‚Äúupgrades‚Äù apparently had the opposite effect. The ship went slower.  And shortly afterward, the automobile titan sold his ‚ÄúBluebird of happiness.‚Äù

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Henry Ford, Thomas Edison, Harvey Firestone, and the famous naturalist John Burroughs called themselves the ‚ÄúFour Vagabonds.‚Äù And they took a series of summer trips together.  The 1924 trip on the Sialia was to Michigan‚Äôs Upper Peninsula.  https://t.co/yQyTLWINJ4

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: Ford owned the Sialia from 1920 to 1927. Every time he boarded, the ship raised a flag that said ‚ÄúBluebird of Happiness.‚Äù The Sialia crisscrossed the upper midwest during this era.  And in 1924 it was involved in one of Ford‚Äôs famous ‚ÄúVagabonds‚Äù trips.

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: So Henry Ford bought the yacht. But nearly as soon as Ford bought it, the yacht was commandeered by the U.S. Navy for use in World War I. It remained in Uncle Sam‚Äôs service for three years.  The ship survived the war‚Ä¶and Ford re-purchased it in 1920.

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: In 1917, Henry Ford himself took an interest in the yacht. Ford‚Äôs interest may have been related to the name.   Sialia is the genus name for bluebirds.  And Ford apparently had a formative childhood memory about seeing a bluebird nest with his father:  https://t.co/Lh9kl1txKU

name: Avi Wolfman-Arent
tweet: The Sialia was built for a Chicago inventor and industrialist named J.K. Stewart ‚Äî who was probably most famous for mass-producing speedometers.   Stewart‚Äôs speedometers were used in the Ford Model T.  More on Stewart's unusual life here:  https://t.co/v8N6EgViCj  https://t.co/n0pRLZovFV

name: Zack Ford
tweet: We must do better. We must stand up for the doctors working to help trans kids. We must defend the families just trying to do right by their children. We must spotlight the trans kids who are absolutely THRIVING thanks to the ability to transition.  We must fight back. 17/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: This is NOT fringe Twitter hate. This is the language that has led states like Florida and Texas to try to investigate families who might affirm their trans kids as child abusers. Families are fleeing for their safety because of these witch hunts. 16/x  https://t.co/EjIMMbjBjD

name: Zack Ford
tweet: And here are even more. I would remind you that @Twitter has instituted a policy of blocking the use of "groomer" as an anti-LGBTQ slur, which it's clearly doing a great job of enforcing:  https://t.co/hOB5GWvL2J 15/x  https://t.co/JgOfaGDVSR

name: Zack Ford
tweet: And here are some more people calling me a child predator for *checks notes* standing with all major medical organizations about the affirming care trans kids deserve. 14/x  https://t.co/ms2AfBDQai

name: Zack Ford
tweet: The understanding among this crowd is that anyone who stands with trans kids is a de facto THREAT to all children. They like child porn, they like to "groom" and molest kids, they should go to jail ‚Äî or worse. Here's a sampling of those kind of responses I got this week. 13/x  https://t.co/lceOcn2huW

name: Zack Ford
tweet: I would also point back to Mr. Dael's tweet there, which says the quiet part out loud. While many claim their only concern is children, these campaigns are about all trans people. The trans adults just get painted as harmful to the trans kids. And with that segue... 12/x  https://t.co/Xd1fsiRTVV

name: Zack Ford
tweet: For a complete debunking of the myth that kids grow out of being trans ‚Äî or "desist" in their trans identity ‚Äî read my feature investigation from FIVE YEARS AGO:  https://t.co/ixmTK1Z4gq  Since then, we've only learned more about how trans kids benefit from affirming care. 11/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: We know that kids as young as 3 have an understanding of their gender:  https://t.co/eCrsnlDTeF  Many still insist however that kids are too young to know they're trans and that they'll grow out of it. They insist on torturing them through a dysphoric puberty first. 10/x  https://t.co/BUMQ0razQs

name: Zack Ford
tweet: To be clear, the response to detransitioners must be to improve care for trans kids, not eliminate it. We want to make sure all people are receiving the right care at the right time, and we can work together to make the regret rates even lower without denying care to others. 9/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: We know that regret rates for transitioning are astonishingly low (~1%):  https://t.co/Rcs4t8XQTy.  The comments that focus on detransitioners speak to how much the media has helped the anti-trans movement by giving disproportionate attention to a very small minority. 8/x  https://t.co/AFwpXv0ml9

name: Zack Ford
tweet: We know trans people overwhelmingly benefit from transitioning:  https://t.co/c9z5yUpWA4  The goal of these posts though is to suggest this kind of surgery is bad (mutilation/chop off/etc.) even though they'd never use the same terms for other surgeries that help people. 7/x  https://t.co/Xj8EoasRfJ

name: Zack Ford
tweet: So here's the original GAG tweet that pointed its 103K followers to my account for harassment. I was describing how threats to hospitals for treating trans kids were making it harder for ALL trans people (not just kids) to access the care they need and deserve. 6/x  https://t.co/JfpRFI1B1L

name: Zack Ford
tweet: One last thing before I show the examples: This is only a fraction of what some people get. I'm a cis guy, so I have it easy. Some trans people or parents of trans kids see this and worse on a weekly if not daily basis. I'm under no illusion I'm the primary victim here. 5/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: I also want to illustrate why people are talking about "stochastic terrorism," because these replies demonstrate how quick many are to see trans allies as violent criminals that need to be stopped by any means necessary to protect kids.  https://t.co/6sC6koJjkF HT: @froomkin 4/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: So much of this ignorance and intolerance could have been avoided if more folks took up the mantle to defend trans people and help make them more visible. This is stuff I and other trans activists and allies were writing about YEARS ago ‚Äî shouting into the void. 3/x

name: Zack Ford
tweet: To be clear: Yes, I know Twitter's a terrible place. No, this isn't a "but my mentions" complaint about ratioing. I want to shine a spotlight on the kind of LANGUAGE that is used against those who stand with trans kids and the affirming care they deserve. 2/x

name: Zack Ford

tweet: 15.#Jaguars DL Dawuane Smoot: ‚ÄúI feel like we‚Äôre finally starting to get it. We just started. It‚Äôs only three. We still have a long season to go. But I feel like we‚Äôre turning the corner to being something special.‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 14.#Jaguars S Rayshawn Jenkins: ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs a huge confidence-builder for our football team, especially putting together two back-to-back dominant wins. I feel like that‚Äôs really a step forward. Now we know we can go into hostile environments and be able to come out on top.‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 13.#Jaguars rookie LB Devin Lloyd had an interception and three passes defensed Sunday after having an interception and three passes defensed in Week 2 against Indianapolis.

name: John Oehser
tweet: 12.The #Jaguars had two takeaways and no giveaways Sunday. They are plus-seven in giveaway-takeaway in 2022 after finishing last in the NFL at minus-20 in 2021. They have eight takeaways in three games after having a league-low nine in 2021. ‚Ä¶

name: John Oehser
tweet: 11.#Jaguars QB Trevor Lawrence wasn‚Äôt sacked and was hurried just twice Sunday; HC Doug Pederson: ‚ÄúThe offensive line gave him protection. When they give him the protection, and we have the skill guys to get open, he's going to find them. That's where it starts.‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 10.The #Jaguars‚Äô defense, after allowing four touchdown passes to Commanders QB Carson Wentz in Week 1, has allowed 10 points in the last two games ‚Äì a 38-10 victory over the Chargers Sunday and a 24-0 Week 2 victory over the Colts; LB Foye Oluokun: ‚ÄúWhen we‚Äôre on, we‚Äôre on‚Ä¶‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 9.#Jaguars QB Trevor Lawrence completed 28 of 39 passes for 262 yards and three touchdowns with no interceptions Sunday. He has thrown six touchdown passes with one interception this season after throwing 12 touchdowns and 17 interceptions in his 2021 rookie season.

name: John Oehser
tweet: 8.The Jaguars on Sunday turned a 16-10 third-quarter lead into a 38-16 lead with touchdowns on three consecutive offensive possessions; HC Doug Pederson: ‚ÄúIt's how we finished this game. These guys are playing with confidence. Winning can do that.‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 7.The #Jaguars have won their last two games by a total of 52 points ‚Äì 38-10 over the Chargers Sunday and 24-0 over the Indianapolis Colts in Week 2. That‚Äôs their widest margin of victory in back-to-back games since 2000.

name: John Oehser
tweet: 6.#Jaguars QB Trevor Lawrence: ‚ÄúThe way we have played, you can't deny that we are a really good team. It doesn't matter what they say about us; we know who we are. Our only goal on Sunday is to win the game, and the way people think about us, it doesn't matter.‚Äù

name: John Oehser
tweet: 5.The #Jaguars remain in first place in the AFC South at 2-1 ‚Äì ahead of the Indianapolis Colts (1-1-1), Tennessee Titans (1-2) and Houston Texans (0-2-1).

name: John Oehser
tweet: 4.#Jaguars HC Doug Pederson: ‚ÄúThis was a great win against a really good football team. This was a playoff-caliber football team. We're still young and we're still learning how to win and how to do all that stuff. I think this was just a great step in that direction."

name: John Oehser
tweet: 3.The #Jaguars hadn‚Äôt won on the road since December 2019, with Sunday‚Äôs victory over the Chargers marking their first back-to-back victories in the same regular season since October 2019. ‚Ä¶

name: John Oehser
tweet: 2.#Jaguars HC Doug Pederson: ‚ÄúI'm just so proud of these guys. They're beginning to see just what it takes to win in this league. It takes the hard work and preparation. They're starting to come together as a football team and that's all I can ask for.‚Äù
